Ebola Hemorrhagic Fever in Uganda - WHO Update 31
-------------------------------------------------
As of Fri 24 Nov 2000, the Ugandan Ministry of Health has reported the
following laboratory-confirmed cases during the past week, 17-23 November:
In Gulu district, there have been 15 confirmed cases. During the week,
there were 14 deaths. The Ugandan Ministry of Health has reported
cumulative figures of 337 cases, including 121 deaths.
In Mbarara district, there have been no new confirmed cases: the total is
3. Since the previous report, the remaining 2 confirmed cases have died.
In Masindi district, 4 new confirmed cases have been reported. These cases
had contact with the first case, before control measures were implemented.
